<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-40-0365 </DOCNO><TEXT>The advantages of forming a wind energy association in Canada are discussedfrom the viewpoint of a wind energy association already established inthe USA. These benefits are: protection from adverse government policies,through providing a lobbying function with government bodies; ensuringunity and cooperation among industry members in efforts to encouragedevelopment of a balanced, worthwhile wind energy program; providinginformation to legislators, prospective wind energy consumers, and industrymembers; representation of the wind energy industry's point of view beforegovernments and the media; providing a forum where industry members cancome together and exchange views, and investigate commercial opportunities;and providing the wind energy industry with political sophistication.</TEXT></DOC>